*Plan & deliverables:* At the outset of this week, I met with Dr. Song to establish a plan for the week. We determined that I would focus on three primary deliverables for this week, detailed below: (1) primer designs targeting _GBA1_ N370S; (2) a graphical abstract for the Familial PD INTERACT document; (3) a battery of tests to evaluate _GBA1_ correction _in vitro_. Additional focuses included establishing long-term goals of increasing my fluency with gene editing and iPSC reprogramming techniques and literature, as well as completing my onboarding. 

\


= N370S primer designs

I designed two primers targeting the _GBA1_ N370S mutation based on project parameters that we established: an amplicon length between 200--700 bp incorporating intronic differences between _GBA1_ and the pseudogene _GBAP1_ to facilitate their bioinformatic distinction downstream. I designed these primers using NCBI primer-BLAST; the exact method and final primers are detailed in the #underline()[attached document.] With Dr. Song's approval, I emailed these to Kiara (David Liu Lab) for her feedback. Once I have Kiara's feedback and confirmation on these primers, I will ensure they are incorporated into the lab's documentation on #text(font: "New Computer Modern Mono")[Teams > Open Lab].

= INTERACT graphical abstract

I consulted with Dr. Song to draft a suitable graphical abstract for incorporation into the Familial PD INTERACT document. We determined that hewing to Dr. Song's original design on the project workflow made sense, with a particular point of emphasis on the one main addition to this workflow (for which we are seeking approval): the gene editing component ("One-step strategy"). Once Dr. Song had approved my draft, I rendered the final image by hand and aseembled the figure in PowerPoint to ensure it will be easily manipulable for future presentations. My final edit is ensuring that the depiction of the reprogramming factors is more identifiably mRNA, per my discussion with Dr. Song. The final figure is #underline()[attached].

